cs.NA, cs.DC, cs.MS, cs.PF, cs.SC 

This paper is about a parallel-in-time integration method, which is commonly used in numerical analysis and scientific computing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). The paper also discusses the implementation of the method using OpenMP, which is a shared-memory parallelization technique. This suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) or cs.SC (Scientific Computing). Additionally, the paper compares the energy consumption and memory footprint of the OpenMP implementation, which could fall under cs.MS (Measurement Science) or cs.PF (Performance).
